<L>__{exterior dusty field day}
<A>__{butch continues his hell bent brisk pace in the field of dirt clods. it's all phillip can do to keep up.}
<C>__{phillip}
<D>__{where we goin'?}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{we're goin' trick r' treatin', phillip.}
<A>__{phillip stops dead in his tracks. butch, sensing that the boy is no longer following, stops, spins and faces phillip.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{what?}
<C>__{phillip}
<D>__{we ain't allowed to trick r' treat.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{huh?}
<C>__{phillip}
<D>__{my mama don't allow it.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{trick r' treatin'? why not?}
<C>__{phillip}
<D>__{against our religion.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{against yer' religion. what kind of foolishness is that?}
<C>__{phillip}
<D>__{jehovah witness.}
<A>__{butch picks up a dirt clod and hurls it as far as he can. he sighs and turns to phillip.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{now, i'm askin' you, phillip. i ain't askin' yer' mother and i ain't askin' jehovah. do you wanna' go trick r' treatin' or not?}
